	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There's only minimal overlap:
<br />4016.2 is microphone bit (Read only) on a Famicom
<br />4016.2 is VROM Bank Select (Write only) in a VS unisystem arcade machine
<br />the other adjacent bits are VS Dipswitches.  No clue how the Microphone polling code works, whether it can be affected by bits other than the microphone bit.
<br />
<br />I'm sure Nintendo took out the microphone polling code from the cartridge versions.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


